"{\"uid\": \"athens-times.com-2024-olympic-games-the-greek-account-of-the-13th-day\", \"text\": \"Athens Times  -  With just 2 entries completed the 13th day for Team Hellas in the , with the Women's National Pole losing to Hungary, but also Daurin Kurugliev excluded from quarterfinals in free wrestling. In particular Thursday (8/08/24) was \\\"poor\\\" in terms of participations, compared to the previous days for our country at the Olympics, as Greek representation was only in 2 sports. Daurin Kurugliev played in 2 games, having a win and a defeat, with him claiming bronze through the reseasons. On the other hand, the National Women's Pole failed against Hungary, after meeting the 12-9 defeat and will compete for the 7-8 positions. Analytical Pale Dauren Kurugliev qualified for the quarter-final of the 86 kg category in the free struggle of the Olympic Games \\\"Paris 2024\\\". In the match for the \\\"phase of 16\\\", the Greek billion European champion beat Ethan Edrian Ramos from Puerto Rico 11-0 and continues his course in the world's top event At \\\"8\\\", Kurugliev found\\u2026 an early big opponent on his way, resulting in his defeat. The \\\"silver\\\" in Tokyo at 86k. and \\\"gold\\\" at Rio de Janeiro at 74k., Hassan Yazdanitsarati, took the 9-4 victory and cut the Greek wrestler's road to gold. However, the Iranian defeated Miles Nazem Aminee from San Marino 7-1 in the semi-finals, qualified for the final and \\\"drawed\\\" with him. On Friday morning (9/8), the Greek champion will face in the first series of replays starting at 12:00 Australian Jaden Alexander Lawrence (2nd match) and if qualified, he will claim a bronze medal against Amine. POOL OF WOMEN One more at the Paris Olympics. Although it started well, the representative band was defeated 12-9 by Hungary in a ranking match and now will claim Saturday morning (10/8, 10:00) seventh place, against Canada. Friday (9/08/24) will be richer in terms of participation.  Athens Times  News about Greece and the World.\"}"